text:
For the CTA that is linking within the page simply link to the full url plus #id-of-the-element-you-want-to-scroll-to

If you want it to smooth scroll most smooth scroll libraries will simply detect the # in the url and simply smooth scroll to that destination.

Then if you want to trigger the video modal, I would use a query parameter in the url like this

`YOUR_PAGE_URL/?openvid=true`

Then in the template drop a hubl module in or use a custom module if it makes sense, and simply ```{% if request.query_dict.openvid %}
&lt;script&gt;
YOUR CODE TO TRIGGER THE MODAL
&lt;/script&gt;
{%endif%}```
